External morphology. Crown (
Figs 1–3
) slightly produced; surface finely granulose; anterior margin broadly rounded; without carina at transition from crown to face; median length of crown approximately four­tenths interocular width and three­tenths transocular width. Ocelli (
Figs 1–3
) located slightly behind imaginary transversal line between anterior eye angles; each ocellus approximately equidistant from median line of crown and adjacent eye angle. Antennal ledges slightly protuberant in dorsal view; dorsal margin oblique, not carinate, descending anteriorly in lateral view. Frons flattened; disc surface finely granulose; muscle impressions distinct. Epistomal suture incomplete along small median distance. Clypeus with contour of its inferior portion forming angle with remain­ der of face; disc setose.

Pronotum (
Figs 1–3
) width slightly greater than transocular width of head; disc finely transversely striated; lateral margins convergent anteriorly; posterior margin very slightly concave. Mesonotum (
Figs 1–3
) smooth, finely transversely striated behind transverse sulcus. Forewings (
Figs 1–3
) opaque and smooth; without distinct membrane; without anteapical plexus of veins; with three closed anteapical cells and five apical cells; base of third apical cell more distal than all other apical cell bases. Hindlegs with femoral apex setal formula 2 : 1 : 1 ; basal tarsomere approximately as long as combined length of two more distal tarsomeres; plantar surface with two parallel rows of undifferentiated setae.

Coloration. Head and thorax mostly black (
Figs 1–3
). Forewings (
Figs 1–3
) red with maculae on corium and clavus and large apical area, dark brown to black.
